'''Alvaro Joshua Lamas''' (born December 19, 1983) is an American actor.

==Career==
Lamas is best known for his role as Rafael Ortega on ''[[As the World Turns]]'',<ref name="people">{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20145816,00.html|title=As the World Turns' A.J. Lamas - As the World Turns : People.com|publisher=people.com|accessdate=2014-05-03}}</ref> Simon McCrae on ''[[Gigantic (TV series)|Gigantic]]'', and as Cisco Gonzalez on ''[[American Family (2002 TV series)|American Family]]''. He also appeared with his family on the [[E!]] reality show ''[[Leave It to Lamas]]''.

==Awards==
In 2001 Lamas was awarded Model of the Year and Young Adult Actor of the Year from the International Model & Talent Association.<ref name="soapcentral">{{cite web|url=http://soapcentral.com/atwt/theactors/lamas_aj.php|title=About ATWT: About the Actors &#124; AJ Lamas &#124; As The World Turns @ soapcentral.com|publisher=[[Soapcentral]]|accessdate=2014-05-03}}</ref>
In 2003 he was [[Mr. Golden Globe]] alongside [[Dominik Garcia-Lorido]], daughter of [[Andy García]], at the [[60th Golden Globe Awards]].<ref name="usmagazine">{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/pictures/miss-golden-globes-through-the-years-201331/27271|title=A.J. Lamas Photo - Miss and Mr. Golden Globes Through the Years - Us Weekly|publisher=usmagazine.com|accessdate=2014-05-03}}</ref>

==Personal life==
He is the son of actor [[Lorenzo Lamas]] and brother to model and actress [[Shayne Lamas]], and grandson to [[Fernando Lamas]] and [[Arlene Dahl]].<ref name="people"/>

==Legal Issues==
In 2012 Lamas was accused of breaking into his ex-girlfriend's home (Jessie Schulman) and holding her at bay in the bathroom. Schulman filed a [[restraining order]], claiming she broke up with A.J. and moved on to a new relationship.<ref name="antimusic">{{cite web|url=http://www.antimusic.com/news/12/January/31Reality_Star_AJ_Lamas_Accused_of_Terrorizing_Girlfriend.shtml#.U2TW2ldWCSo|title=Reality Star A.J. Lamas Accused of Terrorizing Girlfriend ::Lamas News ::antiMusic.com|publisher=antimusic.com|accessdate=2014-05-03}}</ref> Lamas denied the incident saying he was only trying to talk to Schulman and work out their relationship.<ref name="antimusic2">{{cite web|url=http://www.antimusic.com/news/12/February/01AJ_Lamas_Denies_Trapping_Ex_In_Bathroom.shtml#.U2TX4ldWCSo|title=A.J. Lamas Denies Trapping Ex In Bathroom ::A.J. Lamas News ::antiMusic.com|publisher=antimusic.com|accessdate=2014-05-03}}</ref>
Later that year Lamas was arrested for [[DUI]]; he pleaded guilty and was sentenced to 36&nbsp;months probation and $1,600 in fines.<ref name="tmz">{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2012/09/09/aj-lamas-arrested-dui/#ixzz30eNQlp00|title=Lorenzo Lamas&#039; Son -- Arrested for DUI &#124; TMZ.com|publisher=tmz.com|accessdate=2014-05-03}}</ref>
In 2015 Lamas was arrested after allegedly shoplifting at [[Target Corporation|Target]] and assaulting a security guard.<ref>http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3229841/Lorenzo-Lamas-son-former-reality-star-J-arrested-allegedly-shoplifting-Target-assaulting-security-guard-carrying-baby.html</ref>

